Heart size is stable. Aortic tortuosity is unchanged. The left humeral head appears inferiorly subluxed with respect to the glenoid however is not visualized adequately on this film and may partially be positional.
Impression: No pneumonia. Improved but persistent mild interstitial edema. Possible subluxation/dislocation of left glenohumeral joint for which dedicated shoulder films can futher characterize.
